1 olive oil
2 potato
20 g butter
1 tomato
1 courgette
1 packet pork mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet Italian Truffle Mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C.
• Cut potato and courgette into bite-sized
chunks, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
Spread out evenly, then roast until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Place the butter in a small heatproof bowl.
Microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Remove tray of veggies from the oven, then
drizzle over melted butter and sprinkle with
grated Parmesan cheese.
• Roast until golden, a further 10-12 minutes.

Little cooks: Add the finishing touch by sprinkling
the cheese on top.

• While the veggies are roasting, combine pork
mince, fine breadcrumbs, the egg, Aussie spice
blend and a pinch of salt in a medium bowl.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of the
mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person).
Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the
ingredients and shaping the mixture into meatballs!

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of
olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and
cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches
if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a
plate and cover to keep warm.

• While the meatballs are cooking, roughly
chop tomato.
• Combine tomato, mixed salad leaves and a
drizzle of balsamic vinegar and olive oil in a
large bowl. Season to taste.

• Divide spiced pork meatballs, cheesy roast
veggies and garden salad between plates.
• Serve with Italian truffle mayonnaise. Enjoy!